Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

Monaco has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Monaco, see Return to the UK
Local measures
You can find more information regarding the measures in place on the Monaco government website (in French).
If you are in Monaco and you believe you have symptoms or have any questions please call Monaco’s coronavirus emergency number 98 98 48 50 or 06 78 63 85 68.
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
You can find more information about cases in Monaco on the TravelHealthPro.
